==English==
=== Etymology ===
From the Latin ''[[disparatus]]'', the past participle of ''[[disparare]]'' "to divide" from ''[[dis-]]'' "apart" + ''[[parare]]'' "prepare"

=== Adverb ===
'''disparately'''
# to act or do in a disparate manner
#: ''the groups were formed intentionally '''disparately'''''

